$=> Postgre SQL

1. Object-relational database
    : Object oriented database + Relational database
    : Similar to relational database
    : Object oriented database -> object , classes & inheritance are supported

2. Open Source
3. Source code is available under PostgreSQL License
4. Building commercial Apps


TYPES OF DATABASES

1. Hierarchical Database
2. NOSQL Database
3. Object oriented Database
4. Relational Database
5. Network Database

$=>  Relational Database

1. Categorized by a set of tables
2. SQL ( Structured Query Language )
    Acts as the application interface
3. Easier to modify
    Extending the Database
    Joining the Database

$: -> OPen Postgre SQl
1. Go to the start
2. Enter psql
3. Then enter the password to start the Postgre Sql
